│ during FoldInst/eraseInstruction do not invalidate the iteration, since  │
│ we're iterating over a separate container of raw pointers captured       │
│ before transformations.                                                  │
│                                                                          │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                           │
│ The crash is caused by erasing non-current instructions in a basic block │
│ while iterating over it using make_early_inc_range. By first collecting  │
│ instruction pointers into a SmallVector and iterating over this stable   │
│ snapshot, we avoid iterator invalidation and prevent the use-after-free  │
│ that leads to the SIGSEGV. The rest of the pass logic, including the     │
│ Worklist-driven processing, remains unchanged, and the fix should        │
│ stabilize the pass for this and similar cases where transformations      │
│ recursively delete multiple instructions within the same block.          │
